Since Confluence 7.11.0, we have introduced the content denormalised function. This is a new feature for faster permissions service to improve page load times.

When performing DB backup, administrators normally use {{mysqldump}} this. This will backup by _default_ all the *triggers* but *NOT* the *stored procedures/functions* which will cause those errors.

What happens here is that the new stored procedures and functions are not added in the backup resulting in the issue mentioned here when this backup is restored.

[https://confluence.atlassian.com/confkb/confluence-mysql-database-migration-causes-content_procedure_for_denormalised_permissions-does-not-exist-error-1072474724.html]

A quick fix for this is to ensure that while performing the mysqldump backup, to add --routines or -R in the {{mysqldump command}}
{code:java}
mysqldump -p db_name --routines > db_backup.sql{code}
{code:java}
mysqldump -p db_name -R > db_backup.sql
{code}
It will be great if the above KB article is linked in the release notes of 7.11 or upgrade notes
 * [https://confluence.atlassian.com/doc/confluence-7-11-upgrade-notes-1035239484.html]
 * [https://confluence.atlassian.com/doc/confluence-7-11-upgrade-notes-1035239484.html]

h3. Problem
Cannot *Save* new Event in the Team Calendars "Create Event" Dialog depending on screen resolution

h3. Environment
Team Calendar version is 7.3.1, which comes with Confluence 7.15.0
MacOS (but also reproduced on PC with resolution 1366x768 and screen size is 13.3" )

h3. Steps to Reproduce
* Create a new Calendar in Team Calendars for Confluence *7.15.0*
* Set the display resolution as below (example on MacOS screenshot attached)


h3. Expected Results
* You should be able to see the *Save* button on the Team Calendars "Create Event" Dialog regardless of the display setting (/)

h3. Actual Results
* The *Save* button is not visible on the eam Calendars "Create Event" Dialog  (x)

h3. Workaround
* Option 1: Zoom Out in the Web Browser seems to offer a viable Workaround
* Option 2: following CSS styles has been used as a workaround in some instances. 
{code}
@media screen and (max-resolution: 100dpi) {
#edit-event-dialog {
margin-top: -310px !important;
}
#edit-event-dialog .dialog-panel-body.calendar-dialog-panel {
height: 500px !important;
}
}
{code}

h3. Problem
Confluence upgrade from 7.4.1 to 7.13.2 fails if the DB server already has another database with Confluence

h3. Steps to Reproduce
Steps to Reproduce
# Create two databases test1 and test2 on the same Oracle server.
# Install Confluence 7.4.1 using test1 database
# Install a separate instance of Confluence 7.4.1 using test2 database
# Upgrade the second instance to Confluence 7.13.2

h3. Expected Results
The upgrade finishes successfully.

h3. Actual Results
2021-11-18 08:51:56,566 ERROR [main] [atlassian.confluence.plugin.PluginFrameworkContextListener] launchUpgrades Upgrade failed, application will not start: Upgrade task com.atlassian.confluence.upgrade.upgradetask.DenormalisedSpacePermissionsUpgradeTask@4478a4ff failed during the SCHEMA_UPGRADE phase due to: StatementCallback; uncategorized SQLException for SQL [DROP INDEX denormalised_space_edit_permissions_denorm_space_sid_idx]; SQL state [72000]; error code [2429]; ORA-02429: cannot drop index used for enforcement of unique/primary key
; nested exception is java.sql.SQLException: ORA-02429: cannot drop index used for enforcement of unique/primary key

h3. Workaround
Remove primary key and index from DENORMALISED tables from test2 database:
{code}
ALTER TABLE "test2"."DENORMALISED_STATE" DROP PRIMARY KEY;
ALTER TABLE "test2"."DENORMALISED_CONTENT" DROP PRIMARY KEY;
ALTER TABLE "test2"."DENORMALISED_SID" DROP PRIMARY KEY;
ALTER TABLE "test2"."DENORMALISED_SPACE_VIEW_PERMISSIONS" DROP PRIMARY KEY;
ALTER TABLE "test2"."DENORMALISED_SPACE_EDIT_PERMISSIONS" DROP PRIMARY KEY;
ALTER TABLE "test2"."DENORMALISED_CONTENT_VIEW_PERMISSIONS" DROP PRIMARY KEY;

DROP INDEX "test2"."DENORM_CONTENT_SPACE_ID_IDX";
DROP INDEX "test2"."DENORM_CONTENT_PARENT_ID_IDX";
DROP INDEX "test2"."DENORMALISED_SID_NAME_TYPE_UNIQ_IDX";
DROP INDEX "test2"."DENORMALISED_SPACE_VIEW_PERMISSIONS_DENORM_SPACE_SID_IDX";
DROP INDEX "test2"."DENORMALISED_SPACE_EDIT_PERMISSIONS_DENORM_SPACE_SID_IDX";
DROP INDEX "test2"."DENORMALISED_CONTENT_VIEW_PERMISSIONS_DENORM_CONTENT_SID_IDX";
{code}

h3. Notes

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *Confluence Server*. Using *Confluence Cloud*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFCLOUD-39114].
  {panel}

